Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.30,0:00:03.19,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As bright as a spark, with a penetratingly precise wit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.19,0:00:04.73,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Once he gets started, you can't stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.73,0:00:06.65,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The case at the Spider House becomes more complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.65,0:00:08.75,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran and Kazuha are in a dangerous situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.75,0:00:10.34,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.34,0:00:12.34,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.34,0:00:15.22,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.19,0:01:41.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We were called out to the Takeda home at Karakuri Pass in Tottori Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.60,0:01:45.62,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Heiji Hattori and Kazuha T≈çyama got lost in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.62,0:01:47.92,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and met up with a foreigner by the name of Robert Taylor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.71,0:01:53.07,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We happened to pass by and find out that we had all been called out to the Takeda home
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.07,0:01:56.50,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}to solve the mystery of the curse at the "Spider House of Karakuri Pass".
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.08,0:02:03.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}On the night we arrive, Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}, the eldest son of the Takeda family,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.60,0:02:06.54,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}committed suicide on the second floor of the puppet warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.54,0:02:10.03,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then someone suspicious appeared behind Kazuha...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.20,0:02:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery of the Spider House of Tottori (The Suspicion)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.19,0:02:24.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! I found the mascot I was looking for!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.95,0:02:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was caught on the lid of the CD player...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.71,0:02:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}? Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.20,0:02:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s penlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.10,0:02:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.87,0:02:40.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}? Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.39,0:02:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, check this out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.25,0:02:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like he's been hit on the back of the head with something!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.58,0:02:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.95,0:02:54.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the killer hit him, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.28,0:02:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The estimated time of death is about 9:00 PM,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.34,0:03:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,just around the time Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.60,0:03:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, he had already been called out by the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.17,0:03:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer met Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here and hit him on the head,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.67,0:03:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,knocking him unconscious, then strung him up by the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.65,0:03:17.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Then he tangled the body up in strings
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.90,0:03:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make it look like the "Spider Mistress" curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.79,0:03:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I still don't get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.98,0:03:29.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did the killer escape from the room after committing the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.12,0:03:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s sandals and flashlight scattered on the floor also bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.83,0:03:40.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's also strange that there's no dust on the shelves and floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.37,0:03:43.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The room was supposed to have been left alone for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.00,0:03:44.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:47.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that small window...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.98,0:03:52.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just about big enough for a kid to get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.19,0:03:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think it's important? Was it left open for a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.63,0:03:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No... I thought I heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.22,0:04:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran's voice just outside the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.60,0:04:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}'s voice too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.67,0:04:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot. Those two are probably in their room, fast asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.01,0:04:12.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.73,0:04:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.08,0:04:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone's coming up the stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.87,0:04:23.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Heavy feet... It's not Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.22,0:04:27.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who'd be coming here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.83,0:04:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.65,0:04:33.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's meet him in person and ask what the reason is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.75,0:04:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's the housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.27,0:04:39.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.21,0:04:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you'd be hungry, so I brought you some rice balls and tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.88,0:04:46.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this looks delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.77,0:04:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}? Are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.87,0:04:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're here, answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.20,0:04:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.26,0:05:02.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you were friends with Misa Takeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the girl who died three years ago?{EOW 98}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.07,0:05:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. We were nurses at the same hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.23,0:05:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the work was too hard for me, and I quit...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.94,0:05:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I became a housekeeper here through Misa's introduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.40,0:05:16.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.95,0:05:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misa was a really nice girl, always attentive and kind...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.76,0:05:24.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.76,0:05:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why does a person like that have to commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.00,0:05:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just maybe... it could be because of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.35,0:05:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misa's father, Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, came home from the hospital for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.09,0:05:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He grabbed his wife, Kinuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and was very angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.90,0:05:46.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said, "You really deceived me for the past 20 years!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.80,0:05:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deceived him? About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.04,0:05:53.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I have no idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.80,0:05:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's when Misa got badly hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.16,0:05:58.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Badly hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.60,0:05:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.82,0:06:04.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misa went between them to stop the fight, but Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} pushed her away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.14,0:06:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She hit her head on a pillar, and had to have seven stitches in her forehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.65,0:06:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misa became gloomy, and rested from work at the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.13,0:06:16.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,until she met Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.34,0:06:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Robert?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.81,0:06:18.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.52,0:06:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The day of a landslide three years ago, Misa happened on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.16,0:06:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was caught in a landslide while taking pictures, and was badly hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.84,0:06:32.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, the hospital rooms were full that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.86,0:06:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misa had no choice, so she had him treated at the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.10,0:06:38.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and brought him here and took care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:42.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, she had a hard time taking care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.14,0:06:43.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inside of Robert's mouth was cut up from the landslide,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.82,0:06:46.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he couldn't speak well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.93,0:06:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Robert could speak Japanese, but it seems he couldn't read or write it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.33,0:06:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the conversation with Misa took place on paper with Roman letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.30,0:07:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when Robert got better and was able to talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.54,0:07:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they seemed to be enjoying things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.73,0:07:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They told all sorts of jokes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.55,0:07:08.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Japanese foods are delicious, especially on rainy days,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.96,0:07:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,dirt and sand are excellent"{o.O?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.43,0:07:16.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm a prince of a certain country, and I came to find a bride who is like light"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.96,0:07:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the time Robert's wounds had healed and a farewell party was to be held,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.51,0:07:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ry≈´ji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and his family were home, and he became friends with them too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.82,0:07:28.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misa also became bright again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.62,0:07:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that makes it more confusing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.85,0:07:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it two or three days after Robert went home that Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} committed suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.80,0:07:39.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't really know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.55,0:07:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but after Robert went home, Misa became gloomy again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.87,0:07:48.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She suddenly disappeared, and everyone thought she ran away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.53,0:07:53.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y≈´z≈ç{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the one who found Misa dead on the second floor of the warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.03,0:07:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And several days later,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.62,0:08:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,her mother, Kinuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, also committed suicide in the warehouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.92,0:08:08.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the two died, was there anybody who had a change in attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.42,0:08:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.98,0:08:15.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came to the funeral without tears or sad expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.93,0:08:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but on the other hand, Ry≈´ji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the one who was a big problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.40,0:08:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He cried in a voice so loud it echoed throughout the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.95,0:08:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The others would be Sae{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and Emi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.01,0:08:30.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, those twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.35,0:08:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two of them were such good friends with Robert,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.65,0:08:38.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but two years ago, when they came back to visit,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.21,0:08:40.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they suddenly started saying something strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.82,0:08:43.91,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It was Robert...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.91,0:08:46.40,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Robert is the one who killed Misa{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-neechan{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.40,0:08:47.60,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Isn't it terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.60,0:08:48.80,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Terrible, terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.90,0:08:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did the children say something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.86,0:08:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.29,0:08:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who came to pick up the dolls, was also surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.43,0:09:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because after they talked to him, they suddenly started saying those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.88,0:09:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did they talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.59,0:09:06.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.87,0:09:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said they only asked him his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.50,0:09:16.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who died in the shed the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.25,0:09:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone was out to attend to the neighborhood gathering.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.67,0:09:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y≈çko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came home ahead of the others to prepare dinner and found him in the shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.94,0:09:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you around then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.70,0:09:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was with Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, buying groceries at the supermarket for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.75,0:09:35.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.17,0:09:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.72,0:09:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After his wife died, Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took over the household finances.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.05,0:09:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, the rope used to hang Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and the string around him,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,can they be found in this warehouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.91,0:09:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, for the string...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.75,0:09:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there's a lot of it because it's used to make the marionettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.43,0:10:01.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ropes are in the shed. Would you like to go and see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.33,0:10:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gee, it's raining hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.79,0:10:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kud≈ç, do you know who the killer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.37,0:10:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope... Not who the killer is, or the locked room trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.89,0:10:15.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not a single lead...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.71,0:10:18.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left the living room,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.94,0:10:22.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Robert went to the shed to get the car, and left with Ran and Kazuha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.09,0:10:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't go near the warehouse even once. It couldn't be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.98,0:10:29.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y≈çko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was in the bath with the twins,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.33,0:10:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the housekeeper who was cleaning up in the living room with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.45,0:10:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the old lady who was in her room, are also clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.66,0:10:36.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.30,0:10:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only ones who could have done anything are Ry≈´ji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the one making the bath...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.67,0:10:46.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Y≈´z≈ç{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was looking all over the house for Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.04,0:10:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But something bugs me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.63,0:10:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.50,0:10:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The string, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.09,0:10:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.17,0:11:02.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did the killer have to use the string to make it look like a curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.16,0:11:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.19,0:11:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he didn't do that, we would have thought it was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.60,0:11:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that request letter that was sent to you also bothers me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.88,0:11:14.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.86,0:11:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was sent by the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.16,0:11:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he taking me lightly and challenging me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.85,0:11:26.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something fishy about this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, the rope...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.70,0:11:32.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is somebody there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.06,0:11:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.66,0:11:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Kazuha's missing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.70,0:11:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.71,0:11:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Only her penlight was on the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.44,0:11:48.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought someone carried her off and panicked...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.01,0:11:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's split up and look for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.29,0:11:57.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha! Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.37,0:11:58.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.48,0:12:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.49,0:12:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, have you found her?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.79,0:12:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No... She's nowhere to be seen!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.85,0:12:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Hattori?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.79,0:12:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door to the warehouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.53,0:12:18.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I closed it, but it's open!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.74,0:12:28.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.96,0:12:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,K...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.93,0:12:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.93,0:12:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.45,0:12:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hang in there, Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.33,0:12:45.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha! Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.51,0:12:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.06,0:12:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.93,0:12:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.63,0:12:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What... happened to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.59,0:13:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember... waiting for Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} in front of the warehouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.50,0:13:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suddenly felt faint...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.52,0:13:04.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be quiet! I'll cut you loose right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,K-Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.82,0:13:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.98,0:13:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like you were just hanging with the strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.42,0:13:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry! I'm so sorry, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.29,0:13:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't search hard enough, and got you into this terrible situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.45,0:13:20.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then... The mascot...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.55,0:13:22.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry... I found it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.59,0:13:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was caught on the lid of my CD player.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.85,0:13:28.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry... If I'd taken a closer look...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.28,0:13:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you found it. Don't lose it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.19,0:13:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hattori...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.70,0:13:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:41.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Old man, please take care of Kazuha.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.95,0:13:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.14,0:13:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.90,0:13:49.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer tried to use our blind spot by hanging Kazuha up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.76,0:13:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in the warehouse we were in a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.89,0:13:58.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After leaving, the killer brought Kazuha here, and wrapped her in the strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.22,0:14:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then all that remained was to put that rope around her neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.23,0:14:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the curse would be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.01,0:14:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one reason the killer had to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.86,0:14:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer noticed my footsteps when I ran over here, and left in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.12,0:14:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the killer is still here, in the warehouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.74,0:14:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kud≈ç. Are my deductions wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.55,0:14:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope. Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.47,0:14:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, let's take a look at the killer's face!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.31,0:14:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is he around?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.71,0:14:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.89,0:14:48.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange. It hasn't been 3 minutes since we came to this warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.28,0:14:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were guarding the entrance on the first floor, so there's nowhere to hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.33,0:14:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only place to escape would be that tiny window.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.64,0:14:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it really possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.64,0:15:02.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a way to get out through there in such a short time?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.67,0:15:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time that girl from Osaka was attacked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.62,0:15:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-By who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.79,0:15:11.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.59,0:15:16.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha is resting in the room right now, but she may remember in time...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.78,0:15:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...one of the faces among you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.18,0:15:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One reason we had you gather here
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.10,0:15:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was to prevent any more murders from taking place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.82,0:15:30.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other was to confirm your alibis!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.88,0:15:35.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alibis? We were asleep in our rooms all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.99,0:15:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.38,0:15:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in my room too, but I wasn't asleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.88,0:15:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you? I didn't see you when we were searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.63,0:15:49.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was searching outside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.16,0:15:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, nobody has an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.67,0:15:54.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You're kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.90,0:15:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Y≈´z≈ç{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s not around...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.69,0:16:01.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y≈´z≈ç? Wouldn't he be in the workshop?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.90,0:16:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.96,0:16:07.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was here working the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.65,0:16:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was putting the finishing touches on the doll Brother had to complete by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.92,0:16:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can make dolls too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.73,0:16:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three years ago, my company went bankrupt, and I came back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.25,0:16:30.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother taught me all sorts of things and let me do the simple constructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.07,0:16:33.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three years ago... That's the time of that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.27,0:16:38.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I came home just after Robert left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.34,0:16:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I wasn't allowed to make fixtures{?} or do repairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.25,0:16:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother's marionettes cost ¬•1,000,000 apiece, and he charged ¬•700,000 for repairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.79,0:16:54.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sold them for ¬•1,000,000 and repaired them for ¬•700,000?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.21,0:16:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can he do business like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.86,0:16:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.89,0:17:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems like there are some people who request repairs more than ten times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.80,0:17:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He charged quite a bit for the marionettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.05,0:17:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the money he made, he often went abroad with Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.21,0:17:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After leaving the sales to Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the dolls began to command high prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:26.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's that big doll?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.96,0:17:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's the marionette of the "spider empress".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.60,0:17:38.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Father was alive, dolls of that size were used at every festival
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.05,0:17:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to do plays of the "spider empress".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.10,0:17:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the number of people able to handle dolls that big gradually disappeared{oi, oi.},
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.65,0:17:46.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and they quit doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.83,0:17:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are those boxes that are stacked up?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.98,0:17:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, those are the dolls that Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was supposed to take that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.30,0:18:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died, Brother realized he was one doll short.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.19,0:18:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The customer called directly and he had to make one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.67,0:18:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.29,0:18:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,please stay in the room everyone is gathered in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.45,0:18:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous to be by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.55,0:18:18.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.93,0:18:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, now's our chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.56,0:18:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The repair fees for the dolls are extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.35,0:18:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite the price, there are customers who request repairs more than 10 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.40,0:18:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A simple puppet that's expensive means
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.98,0:18:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,what's inside is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.47,0:18:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,narcotics!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the marionettes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.65,0:18:48.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you can only put the narcotics in the head, so the price is cheaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.01,0:18:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.86,0:18:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I know why Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called a detective
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.00,0:18:56.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to find out who the killer was.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.54,0:19:00.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A large part of the entire picture has come into view.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.34,0:19:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's left that we don't know is the locked room trick
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.48,0:19:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and why Kazuha was attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.99,0:19:11.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sae? Emi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.24,0:19:13.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it? What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.60,0:19:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two daughters I brought to the restroom aren't here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.32,0:19:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:19.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Mother...\N- Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.34,0:19:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You worried me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.72,0:19:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you to wait in front of the restroom when you were through?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.15,0:19:29.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there was a smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.28,0:19:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There sure was! A funny smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.57,0:19:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably the spider children burning in the furnace!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.20,0:19:35.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.79,0:19:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandmother said so, didn't she...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.40,0:19:39.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She did! She did!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.15,0:19:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furnace?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.06,0:19:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true, there's something strange burning in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.79,0:19:52.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, come to think of it... What was the meaning of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.70,0:19:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said it, didn't you? You called Robert "murderer"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.62,0:19:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The day Robert was leaving,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.32,0:20:02.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} told us to go and ask him what his feelings were,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.65,0:20:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we went to the bus stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.75,0:20:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked him, "How do you feel about Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.75,0:20:12.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Robert wrote a terrible thing down on paper!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.05,0:20:13.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Didn't he?\N- Didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.13,0:20:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Terrible thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.67,0:20:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- He wrote, "die!"\N- He wrote, "die!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.44,0:20:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Die?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.41,0:20:18.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.52,0:20:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Terrible, terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.51,0:20:21.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't let it bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.84,0:20:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The children probably saw wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.81,0:20:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have shown that business card.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.91,0:20:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Business card?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.32,0:20:31.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, I'm sure I have it here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.95,0:20:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.00,0:20:44.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They found this name card inside the wallet and made a lot of noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.69,0:20:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They asked, "Who did you get this from?" "Where is this person?"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.80,0:20:50.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.82,0:20:54.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it out somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.10,0:20:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.80,0:20:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.76,0:21:00.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a stun gun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.81,0:21:03.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.54,0:21:06.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Heiji! I feel much better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.28,0:21:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take off your clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.71,0:21:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just let me see!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.00,0:21:11.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.99,0:21:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.04,0:21:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why am I the only one to get hit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.25,0:21:19.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.89,0:21:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Small burn marks on her back...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.96,0:21:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she {\i1}was{\i0} knocked out with a stun gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.90,0:21:32.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? Did she say anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.03,0:21:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She didn't see the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.59,0:21:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but she said she found a strange ball in front of the warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.40,0:21:36.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.85,0:21:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said it was a ball about this small.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.31,0:21:42.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}BB shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.81,0:21:44.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.89,0:21:46.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I never thought of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.75,0:21:48.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If that's so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.30,0:21:49.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:51.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Should be somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.60,0:21:52.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.22,0:21:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it! Hattori, it's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.79,0:21:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The marks of a thumbtack!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.77,0:22:00.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.05,0:22:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange string with loops on the beam ends!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.09,0:22:07.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just as we thought, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.29,0:22:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.76,0:22:15.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no mistake... That person is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.83,0:23:49.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer didn't need to escape from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.00,0:23:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.95,0:23:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was to avenge Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who committed suicide in this warehouse three years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.20,0:24:01.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s revenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.65,0:24:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one person who could have done it without anyone noticing!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.03,0:24:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.71,0:24:14.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery of the Spider House of Tottori (Case Closed)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.99,0:24:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Roman letters
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.30,0:24:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next time, the solution at last!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.78,0:24:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next time, it'll be the killer who gets caught in the web!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.21,0:24:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
